The identifier code of the graphics device (RO).

This is the PCI device ID of the user's graphics card. Together with SystemInfo.graphicsDeviceVendorID,
this number uniquely identifies a particular graphics card model. The number is the same across operating
systems and driver versions.

See <a href="http://www.pcidatabase.com">pcidatabase.com</a> for a list of device IDs.

SA: SystemInfo.graphicsDeviceVendorID, SystemInfo.graphicsDeviceName.